# Evogent — Environment Configuration
# Copy to .env.local:  cp .env.example .env.local

# ============================================================
# Optional Bird-backed X/Twitter access
# ============================================================
AUTH_TOKEN=
CT0=

# ============================================================
# Brain Provider
# ============================================================
# Evogent's brain provider is selected in data/config.md during
# README.md -> Setup Guide for Coding Agents -> Phase 2.
# The normal install path uses Claude Code or Codex CLI, not provider API keys.
# If you are following the standard install guide, you can leave this section alone.

# ============================================================
# Optional
# ============================================================
# HOST=127.0.0.1
# Listen address. Defaults to 127.0.0.1 (loopback only). Set HOST=0.0.0.0 only if
# you have an authenticated reverse proxy in front of Evogent and have set
# MEDIA_AGENT_TRUST_NETWORK=1.
# PORT=3001                      # Server port
# MEDIA_AGENT_* env vars intentionally keep their legacy prefix for compatibility.
# MEDIA_AGENT_DB_PATH=./data/media-agent.db
# MEDIA_AGENT_TRUST_NETWORK=1
# DANGEROUS unless an authenticated reverse proxy is actually in front. Setting
# this allows non-loopback chat / agent-spawn / write API calls. cloudflared on
# the same host still connects from localhost, so cloudflared by itself is NOT
# the auth proxy - you also need Cloudflare Access policies on every hostname
# that reaches the app. See docs/security.md.

# MEDIA_AGENT_CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN=<team>.cloudflareaccess.com
# Cloudflare Access team domain for JWKS verification of Cf-Access-Jwt-Assertion
# headers. When set, the gate cryptographically verifies the JWT against
# Cloudflare's public keys before trusting tunnel-forwarded identity. Leave
# unset to fall back to header-presence checks (works correctly when cloudflared
# is the only path to the app and Cloudflare strips client-supplied headers).
#
# MEDIA_AGENT_CF_ACCESS_AUD=<application-aud>
# Optional: pin the expected JWT `aud` claim to a specific Cloudflare Access
# Application AUD. If set, JWTs with a different aud are rejected. If unset,
# any valid Cloudflare-Access-signed JWT is accepted (signature proves origin).
